bib_record.title: Gamma coincidence study of 208Pb + 350 MeV 64Ni collisions

free_txt: In- and off-beam gamma coincidence analysis. Analysis
consisted of 11 Compton suppressed Ge detectors and
an inner ball of 48 BGO elements.
80 cm3 Ge(Li) detector in a passive low
350 MeV 64Ni. The cyclotron pulsing was set to 69 ns
spacing between the beam bursts to allow for a clean
separation of in- and off-beam  events.
Half of the sum of production yields in this
30 mg/cm2 thick 208Pb target isotopically enriched to
been established with 10 to 30% accuracy taking into
account all possible sources of errors.
The uncertainty of the absolute cross section scaling
is not included in this error.
50% uncertainty of the absolute cross section
both off-and in-beam coincidence data were used
Production yield is obtained from interpolation of
the results obtained for  the neighbouring nuclei.
